2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the properties of road network systems, which can be considered a type of network architecture. 
3. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper proposes a new method for measuring road network vulnerability using a discrete Ricci curvature, which can be considered a computational engineering approach. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of statistical indicators to analyze road network systems, which can be related to information theory. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new method for characterizing the local and intrinsic properties of a network, which can be considered a data structures and algorithms approach.
